{title: When A Soldier Knocks And Finds Nobody Home}
{artist: Ernest Tubb}
{composer: Written by Ernest Tubb, Moon Mullican, Lou Wayne}

[C]I’m alone with all my sorrow
It’s so [F]hard to face to[C]morrow
Cause I knocked and no one [D7]met me at the [G7]door
I have asked the next door neighbor
What you’ve [F]packed and went [C]away for
But they only say [G7]you don’t live here no [C]more[C7]
When [F]I sailed across the blue
I [C]thought I could count on you
But [D7]I’ve come back home sweetheart to find you [G7]gone
[C]It’s a shame you couldn’t be here
What a [F]sorry sight to [C]see here
When a soldier knocks and [G7]finds nobody [C]home
Repeat #3,4